Class Transaction

java.lang.Object
models.Transaction
public class Transaction extends Object
Represents a financial transaction within the system. Each transaction may be associated with a customer and/or an employee.

    • Transaction

      public Transaction(int id, double amount, Integer customerId, LocalDateTime timestamp, Integer employeeId)
      Constructs a Transaction with all fields specified.
      Parameters:
      id - unique identifier of the transaction
      amount - monetary amount of the transaction
      customerId - ID of the associated customer, or null if none
      timestamp - date and time of the transaction
      employeeId - ID of the employee who processed the transaction, or null if none

    • Transaction

      public Transaction(double amount, Integer customerId, LocalDateTime timestamp, Integer employeeId)
      Constructs a Transaction without an ID (for new transactions).
      Parameters:
      amount - monetary amount of the transaction
      customerId - ID of the associated customer, or null if none
      timestamp - date and time of the transaction
      employeeId - ID of the employee who processed the transaction, or null if none
